## The situation in two minutes

AI has crossed from an equity story into a **credit and financing story**. The five biggest hyperscalers are spending roughly **$750bn on AI infrastructure in 2026** — a 67% year-on-year increase and the third straight year of 60%-plus growth. At those spending levels, operating cash flow no longer covers the bill. Oracle is spending **86% of its revenue on capex**, Meta 54%, and Amazon's free cash flow is projected to turn **negative** this year. So the marginal dollar of AI infrastructure is now **debt-funded** — and that is exactly where your desk lives.

Bond markets are responding. Hyperscalers issued ~$121bn of US bonds in 2025, more than four times their historical average. Barclays' own house view is that 2026 US IG issuance could exceed **$2 trillion** — a post-COVID record. Beyond bonds, a new private-credit and SPV channel has emerged, with deals like **Meta's $30bn Hyperion vehicle** pioneering off-balance-sheet data-centre financing.

For the EU Fund Financing desk, this means: more collateral, more leveraged demand for that collateral via TRS and repo, and more revenue. But it also means every product on the desk is now linked to **one concentrated theme** — which, if it reverses, moves everything at once.

